The paper discusses the economic analysis and pricing models for data collection and wireless communication in IoT, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of intelligent rational decision-making methods, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also touches upon security issues, which is a subfield of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses resource and power optimization, which is a subfield of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of pricing models in crowdsensing applications, which is a subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
